<AboutSection />

<AboutPositionSection>
## About the **Position**

The android developer will help us make our app **_Save_** and archival process as easy-to-use as possible for our users and [Decentralized Archivist Communities (DACs)](https://open-archive.org/programs). 

This role will work with our developer team, executive team, and usability experts to ensure the app is both updated and usable. The team coordinates both synchronously and asynchronously via chat, email, bug trackers, and occasional voice meetings. 

A commitment to free and open-source software, good communication and documentation skills, and a passion for contributing to the greater good are all essential for this role.


</AboutPositionSection>

<DetailsSection>
<DetailItem>
### Responsibilities

The Android Software Engineer for **_Save_** (Kotlin, Java, JavaScript) will:
* Implement and test new features
* Diagnose and fix Android platform-specific issues
* Improve security and privacy properties

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
### Required skills and experience

* Extensive experience with Java, Kotlin, and JavaScript
* Familiarity with working on decentralized backends for mobile: we are planning to implement decentralized archiving options within our app based on Filecoin
* Experience with anti-censorship technologies, especially on mobile platforms
* Keen interest in and experience in peer-to-peer technology stacks (decentralized tech, IPFS, and libp2p, etc.)
* Experience working across time zones and teams (executive, tech, usability, design, etc.)
* Be comfortable working remotely with a geographically distributed team

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
### Nice to Have Skills (not mandatory)
* Experience with Swift and iOS
* Experience working for or with nonprofit or at-risk or marginalized community groups with sensitivities to their localized needs (i.e., understanding their threat models, securing communications, and working well with diverse cultures)


</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Working with us

OpenArchive aims to help people have more agency over the long-term preservation, privacy, management, and access to their mobile media. We are working on challenging, but compelling problems at the crux of privacy, usability, and long-term preservation of mobile media. If you are passionate about helping people create secure, robust, personal archives to preserve mobile media, especially media made by historically marginalized communities, or are just interested in making secure archiving tools more usable, weâ€™d love to hear from you.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Reporting

This position reports to OpenArchive's Tech Lead.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Location

This position is fully remote. OpenArchive operates as a distributed team, with core staff based in the U.S., and others based in Africa, Latin America, and Europe. Overlap with US time-zones is preferred.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Compensation

This is a part-time contractor role for 10-20 hours a week for 6-12 months at the rate of $90 - $125/hour depending on experience. The renewal of the contract and increases in payment are dependent on funding and performance.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Application Process

To apply, please email us the following:

- Your resume;
- A cover letter that explains your interest in the position and why you believe you are well-suited for the role;
- Two references and their contact information (email or phone);
- A link to an example of your relevant work that best represents the competencies outlined here.

</DetailItem>
